laboratory_examinations.findings: Appendix is distended up to 8 mm with hyperemia of the wall and an appendicolith at the base. There is surrounding fluid. Peripherally enhancing hemorrhagic follicle seen in the right ovary. A small amount of free fluid seen in the pelvis. Other organs (liver, spleen, kidneys, adrenal glands, pancreas, gallbladder, stomach, and small bowel) are unremarkable.
laboratory_examinations.changes_over_time: Peripherally enhancing hemorrhagic follicle similar to prior ultrasound.
